aa(lp129
VBut none of them worked.
p130
aVSo what we did was we processed the images together,
p131
aVand we put two images into one blank screen.
p132
aVAnd here are two different images of the Archimedes manuscript.
p133
aVAnd the image on the left
p134
aVis the normal red image.
p135
aVAnd the image on the right is an ultraviolet image.
p136
aVAnd in the image on the right
p137
aVyou might be able to see some of the Archimedes writing.
p138
aVIf you merge them together into one digital canvas,
p139
aVthe parchment is bright in both images
p140
aVand it comes out bright.
p141
aVThe prayer book is dark in both images
p142
aVand it comes out dark.
p143
aVThe Archimedes text is dark in one image and bright in another.
p144
aVAnd it'll come out dark but red,
p145
aVand then you can start to read it rather clearly.
